    "teacher_markdown": "When students change the condition in the `for` loop, they will see the following displayed in the console:\r\n\r\n```\r\nException message: java.lang.ArrayIndexOutOfBoundsException: Index 5 out of bounds for length 5\r\n\t at LoopPainter.paintAndMove(LoopPainter.java:60)\r\n\t at NeighborhoodRunner.main(NeighborhoodRunner.java:13)\r\n```\r\n\r\nThis is because the variable `index` reaches the value that is equivalent to the length of the 1D array `paintColors`, which is one more than the last index in the 1D array.",
